CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 29, 1958, pg. 8, reads: "Attention State Liquor Control Board - How Many More Taverns Can Homewood-Brushton Stand?  One of 'Two-In-One' - One of two taverns within two consecutive blocks on the periphery of the Homewood-Brushton area near Wilkinsburg and Penn Township is Vic and Ralph's in the 8000 block of Frankstown Ave. - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: 8000 block of Frankstown Avenue at Wheeler Street with Vic and Ralph's Beer and Zangrille's Hardware, Homewood
